  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "The Supersaw Fallacy taken to its logical extreme: five unison voices at 0.03 cents detune — the tightest possible spread that still creates width. At this detune level, voices do not fight each other; they reinforce. The result is massive, warm, and transparent simultaneously. Shimmer at 0.5 feedback sits in the middle of the spectrum. This is what clouds look like when they stack vertically: cumulus towering, enormous, internally coherent.",
